						<cell pady="10" width="32">
							<img sh="32" src="ui/zoopedia/fact-bullet.tga" sw="32" sx="0" sy="0" />
						</cell>
						<cell pady="10" width="202">Cartoon animals are the remnants of endangered species after hundreds of millenia of domestication efforts.</cell>
						<br />
						<cell pady="10" width="32">
							<img sh="32" src="ui/zoopedia/fact-bullet.tga" sw="32" sx="0" sy="0" />
						</cell>
						<cell pady="10" width="202">Cartoon animals have been rendered passive and harmless as a result of this intense breeding.</cell>
						<br />
						<cell pady="10" width="32">
							<img sh="32" src="ui/zoopedia/fact-bullet.tga" sw="32" sx="0" sy="0" />
						</cell>
						<cell pady="10" width="202">Some cartoon animals have been selected to be ridden by their human companions.
</cell>
						<br />
					</cell>
				</cell>
				<cell width="340">
  <color r="255" g="248" b="178">To unlock the stone tiger in challenge or campaign games, you must earn a 1-star zoo fame rating for your zoo.</color><p />

In terms of size, there is no ape greater than the cartoon gorilla. They easily outweigh wild gorillas, and have equally impressive strength as a result of their size. Toon gorillas enjoy a lean diet of fish and vegetables to maintain their peak physique.
</cell>
